<subSubSection id="1A9464B0826A10BD47C5C333F55784A5" lastPageId="171" lastPageNumber="172" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E02F30EC724771AD4A4F4A2D4E06FBE2" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5CDE66D3274AC44790CB1E84A7AB05F" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3508A63563FF1FD6759D3A4614A7AC54" captionStart="Figure 155" captionStartId="F155" captionText="Figure 155. Distribution of Conostegia foreroi." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure155" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96513" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">155</figureCitation>
). Endemic to the the departments of Antioquia and 
<normalizedToken id="558CC90D495940B02E571D35E673811F" originalValue="Chocó">Choco</normalizedToken>
in Colombia, 1300-1400 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2ED849F60943727E4582AF34329A2FE3" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973961" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure155" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96513" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" start="Figure 155" startId="F155">
<paragraph id="06BED298CD7483167D270213822E566D" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="EEF114133D43E2A876456A0B6797B902" bold="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Figure 155.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="6E922853E323D464FA68B2136479E971" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis id="C7EC9011D18A9CBE52C9D0B56F6CA9C0" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AD271F3B4C9EC26459BEC76A1322B0B7" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<taxonomicName id="8627EB01C0B0D8135FF2345A96D4CF0E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis id="0DF4FF11CFE03B6A052C045D4BE169EC" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<pageBreakToken id="BB3CE34722F976431ACBD4B12A0E8E40" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
foreroi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very uncommon species characterized by its dense pubescence on stems, leaves, inflorescences and hypanthia. As 
<bibRefCitation id="1A5D8F024140F3278AA1A88B09308E87" author="Wurdack, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="244" pageNumber="245" pagination="293 - 301" refId="B89" refString="Wurdack, JJ, 1988. Certamen Melastomataceis XXXVIII. Phytologia 64 (4): 293 - 301" title="Certamen Melastomataceis XXXVIII." volume="64" year="1988">Wurdack (1988)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned in the protologue, it resembles 
<taxonomicName id="0F16501410947F4504DCEC90EE412198" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia costaricensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costaricensis">
<emphasis id="E99F4D23DA939AD4DB1376625A4CE13C" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia costaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CF37C60F431DD01CE9D443B12338B225" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia petiolaris" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petiolaris">
<emphasis id="F7AE589DEFCD00A59487264474777053" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia petiolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter two species thus also resemble each other but none of the three are closely related based on the molecular phylogeny, evidencing the possible multiple evolutions of shrubby and densely pubescent species. Among the differences between 
<taxonomicName id="6FF087804681069D13D50F4B087DCA77" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis id="47C6708EA0A391FE9DDCE6BE125ECE19" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that help distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName id="F88E1AD35A69A0156B9C820C4548183D" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia costaricensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costaricensis">
<emphasis id="02986E1E7A3D1DF039502E0462C9B7A1" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia costaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C98E99E3B0BC62AA2FC886064D26D142" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia petiolaris" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petiolaris">
<emphasis id="C56598D6C7892215C49ECE7B2D531160" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia petiolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the flattened setae on the nodes, smaller flowers, a sparsely glandular pubescent ovary apex and stamens that have a stronger geniculation. Within section 
<taxonomicName id="63CE6E4315257BAFBD39B394BD941D65" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="D.Don" authorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis id="BCE78BB0127E1FA55110E261E5C833EC" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="214A671B6E5F8597AC8CD47618891DB1" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Wurdack" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia foreroi" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foreroi">
<emphasis id="ED578CF9F4CA4D1BBFA5860F1238528F" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia foreroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to resemble more 
<taxonomicName id="931BD00A0AFAAFB45BAB05A8AFF009AE" authority="D.Don, 1823" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Clidemia hammelii" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hammelii">
<emphasis id="663B63F9D760A40A52956B933C6CE9E4" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Clidemia hammelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species is overall less pubescent and has pocket domatia at the base of the leaf on the abaxial surface. This species appears to also converges with 
<taxonomicName id="D9383BF990ED7AB504CB8FBB92AFEB2F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis id="5BF7FDB3FC1CFC18C8AEEE6CBB45FF38" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
